{"lemma":"طابَ","slug":"طابَ","root":"ط.#.ب","root_slug":"ط-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-_-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طابَ","root":"طيب","pos":"V","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27402","n27407"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to seem suitable, to remit, to do well"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27402","headword_ar":"طَابَ","root":"Tyb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaTiybu","text_ar":"يَطِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, &c.,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiybN","text_ar":"طِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S [but there mentioned app. as a subst.], O, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiybapN","text_ar":"طِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbN","text_ar":"طَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY","text_ar":"طُوبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. infrà] (Ksh and Bd in xiii. 28) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taToyaAbN","text_ar":"تَطْيَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [the last of which is of a measure denoting intensiveness, and is said in the TA to be with fet-h because it is unsound, whereas the inf. n. of a sound verb, if of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tfEAl","text_ar":"تفعال"},{"kind":"text","text":", is with kesr, but this is a strange mistake, (see 2 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byn","text_ar":"بين"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyv","text_ar":"خَبِيث"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in two senses:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant, delightful, delicious, sweet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"savoury;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"la*~a","text_ar":"لَذَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna la*iy*FA","text_ar":"كَانَ لَذِيذًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was esteemed"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant, delightful, delicious, sweet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"savoury, in taste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in odour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, pure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clean."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tay~ibN","text_ar":"طَيِّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbato nafosuhu","text_ar":"طَابَتْ نَفْسُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His mind"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"himself]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerful, happy, pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dilated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from straitness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tibotu bihi","text_ar":"طِبْتُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosFA","text_ar":"نَفْسًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbato bihi nafosiY","text_ar":"طَابَتْ بِهِ نَفْسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my mind, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, cheerful, happy, pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dilated, by means of it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with what next precedes: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleased, content,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"willing, to grant, concede, give,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"do, it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O, K:) [for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbato nafosuhu biAl$~aYo'i","text_ar":"طَابَتْ نَفْسُهُ بِالشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[often] signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He granted, conceded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave, the thing, liberally,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"willingly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his own good pleasure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without constraint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without anger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalotu *`lika","text_ar":"فَعَلْتُ ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biTiybapinafosK","text_ar":"بِطِيبَةِنَفْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of my own free will; willingly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not being constrained by any one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbato nafosiY Ealayohi","text_ar":"طَابَتْ نَفْسِى عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My mind was agreeable to it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; said when a thing is agreeable, or suitable, to one's mind; and [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tibotu nafosFA Ealayohi","text_ar":"طِبْتُ نَفْسًا عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbato nafosuhu liloEamali","text_ar":"طَابَتْ نَفْسُهُ لِلْعَمَلِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wagayorihi","text_ar":"وَغَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was cheerful, happy, pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"willing, to do work &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n$T","text_ar":"نشط"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbato nafosiY Eano *`lika tarokFA","text_ar":"طَابَتْ نَفْسِى عَنْ ذٰلِكَ تَرْكًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was pleased, willing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"content, to leave, give up, relinquish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be without, that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tibotu","text_ar":"طِبْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafosFA Eanohu","text_ar":"نَفْسًا عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": whence, in the Kur [iv. 3],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA_ino Tibona","text_ar":"فَاـِنْ طِبْنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lakumo Eano $aYo'K minohu nafosFA","text_ar":"لَكُمْ عَنْ شَىْءٍ مِنْهُ نَفْسًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"But if they be pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"willing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"content, to give up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relinquish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remit, unto you somewhat thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TAb","text_ar":"طاب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, O, Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiybN","text_ar":"طِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiybapN","text_ar":"طِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lawful, allowable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, O, Msb, K, * TA.) [In the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~iybu","text_ar":"الطِّيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~iybapu","text_ar":"الطِّيبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHil~u","text_ar":"الحِلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which Golius has supposed to mean in this case “ quod licitum, legitimum; ” and which Freytag has in like manner expl. as meaning “ res licita, ” and “ licitum: ” but it is here an inf. n., of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a","text_ar":"حَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; not syn. with the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHalaAlu","text_ar":"الحَلَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is given as an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ay~ibu","text_ar":"الطَّيِّبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAba liY ka*aA","text_ar":"طَابَ لِى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a thing became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has become, lawful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) Hence the saying of Aboo-Hureyreh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AaloA=na TaAba AlD~iraAbu","text_ar":"اَلْا=نَ طَابَ الضِّرَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAba A@moDarobu","text_ar":"طَابَ ا@مْضَرْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) as some relate it, accord. to the dial. of Himyer, (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAb A@lD~arobu","text_ar":"طَاب ا@لضَّرْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Now fighting has become lawful."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA@nokiHuwA maA TaAba lakumo mina A@ln~isaA='i","text_ar":"فَا@نْكِحُوا مَا طَابَ لَكُمْ مِنَ ا@لنِّسَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [iv. 3], means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then take ye in marriage"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are lawful to you"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of women"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbati AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"طَابَتِ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiybN","text_ar":"طِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The land became abundant in herbage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)       -A2-  See also 2, in two places: ―         -b2-  and see 10."}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","Mgh","A","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n27407","headword_ar":"طَابٌ","root":"Tyb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAba","text_ar":"طَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiybN","text_ar":"طِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tay~ibN","text_ar":"طَيِّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.: a poet says, praising 'Omar Ibn-'Abd-El-'Azeez,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"muqaAbalu AlA_iEoraAqi fiY AlT~aAbi AlT~aAbo\n                      \n                     \n                        bayona A^abiY AlEaASiY waA=li AlxaT~aAbo"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rooted by the father's and the mother's side in unsullied goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the like,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between Abu-l- 'Ásee"},{"kind":"text","text":"on the one side"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the family of ElKhattáb"},{"kind":"text","text":"on the other: for it is evidently cited as an ex. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlTAb","text_ar":"الطاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"used as a subst. and as an epithet; so that by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY AlTAb AlTAb","text_ar":"فى الطاب الطاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY","text_ar":"فى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~iybi AlT~ay~ibi","text_ar":"الطِّيبِ الطَّيِّبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": otherwise it might be supposed that the literal repetition is meant to denote simply corroboration, as appears to be the case in an instance which will be mentioned in what follows:] the object of praise being the son of 'Abd-El-'Azeez the son of Marwán the son of El-Hakam the son of Abu-l-'Ás [or 'Ásee], and his mother being Umm-'Ásim the daughter of 'Ásim the son of 'Omar the son of El-Khattáb. (S, O.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*oqu A@boni TaAbK","text_ar":"عَذْقُ ا@بْنِ طَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sort of palm-trees in El-Medeeneh"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. so called because of the sweetness of their fruit, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TAb","text_ar":"طاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"may in this instance be for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbap","text_ar":"طَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", a name of ElMedeeneh]: (K:) or, as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTabu A@boni TaAbK","text_ar":"رُطَبُ ا@بْنِ طَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of dates of El-Medeeneh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu","text_ar":"اِبْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbK","text_ar":"طَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of fresh ripe dates:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*oqu A@boni TaAbK","text_ar":"عَذْقُ ا@بْنِ طَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*oqu A@boni zayodK","text_ar":"عَذْقُ ا@بْنِ زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two sorts of dates:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) accord. to IAth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruTabu A@boni","text_ar":"رُطَبُ ا@بْنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAbK","text_ar":"طَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of dates of El-Medeeneh"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called in relation to Ibn-Táb, a man of its inhabitants. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TAb TAb","text_ar":"طاب طاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [asserted to be]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One of the names of the Prophet in the Gospel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but where said to occur, I know not;] the interpretation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA^* mA^*","text_ar":"ماذ ماذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA* maA*","text_ar":"مَاذ مَاذ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning “ very good in disposition, ” &c.;] the second word corroborating, and denoting intensiveness of signification. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}